$ torchrun --nproc_per_node=2 code/ulysses_demo.py
=================================================================
DeepSpeed-Ulysses Sequence Parallelism Demo
=================================================================

World size: 2 GPUs

Configuration:
  Full sequence length: 8192
  Local sequence per GPU: 4096
  Total attention heads: 8
  Local heads per GPU (after transpose): 4
  Head dimension: 64

-----------------------------------------------------------------
Initial layout (sequence-parallel):
  Q, K, V shape per GPU: (2, 4096, 8, 64)
  Each GPU holds: 4096 tokens, all 8 heads

-----------------------------------------------------------------
After all-to-all (head-parallel):
  Q shape per GPU: (2, 8192, 4, 64)
  Each GPU holds: 8192 tokens, only 4 heads
  -> Now standard attention can be computed!

-----------------------------------------------------------------
After Ulysses attention:
  Output shape per GPU: (2, 4096, 8, 64)
  Back to sequence-parallel layout

-----------------------------------------------------------------
Summary:
  1. Start: each GPU has 4096 tokens × 8 heads
  2. All-to-all #1: transpose to 8192 tokens × 4 heads
  3. Attention: standard self-attention on local heads (no partial softmax!)
  4. All-to-all #2: transpose back to 4096 tokens × 8 heads

Key advantage: No complex partial softmax accumulation like ring attention
=================================================================
